cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GR, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with the computational geometry problem of computing higher-order Voronoi diagrams in a specific metric, namely the city metric induced by quickest paths in the L1 metric in the presence of an accelerating transportation network of axis-parallel line segments. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also presents upper and lower bounds on the structural complexity of the diagrams, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also discusses the special case where k=n-1, which could make it relevant to cs.GR (Graphics) as well. Finally, the paper presents algorithms for computing the diagrams, which could make it relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
